{
  "stem": "5758.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It was a-- the camp-- if you remember before, in 1936 I think, you had a civil war in Spain.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And a lot of the Spanish [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] patriots, I mean, the-- the-- the left-wing Spanish, when Spain was occupied by-- or won-- when Franco won the war, they left as refugees.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they were put by France-- they went over the Pyrenees, went-- were put into this particular camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was approximately 10 kilometers from a town called Perpignan.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we were-- when we were arrested and transported, we were in a train guarded by French soldiers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But not only Jews, but there were real Germans, fifth columnist, which they arrested, and they put us with Nazi Germans into this particular camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We, naturally, Jews, had continuous fight with the fifth columnists, with the Nazi Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And they were very antisemitic and called us names-- [GERMAN], et cetera, and we wouldn't let them do it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we called the camp commander and-- and said, look here, you are putting us together in barracks together with these Nazis.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And you know, you must realize that we are anti-Nazis, that we are refugees from the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We cannot possibly go and stay in a barracks where we have continuous fights.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So he realized.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He got the Jews out, and we got our own barracks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But on the-- [SIGHS] this camp, I must explain, this camp was bordering onto the sea.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "It was-- we had-- there was a beach, but it was all wired up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "That means we couldn't go through into the water.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It was all wired up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And underneath the wires, you know, we saw there was a big concrete-- very large concrete area.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
